cartel is exporting charcoal and harvested trees logged in area forests to Arab countries, Nyeri Senator Ephraim Maina has said. On Sunday he said th business has been going on for 10 to 20 years but has only recently reached an alarming level, prompting area leaders to raise the alarm. Hepraised the government for suspending logging for 90 days. He promised to come up with a bill to address the problem of selective harvesting of trees that have taken 100 years to mature. He said the Aberdare and Mt Kenya forests are the worst hit, making major rivers like Tana River shrink to about 10 per cent of their original size. The senator said something has to be done before the country turns into a desert.